Commentary Text: Washington Sundar to Aman Hakim Khan, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! What a horrendous shot. I'm sure Ponting will not be too happy, and the camera points to DC's head coach who is chewing on his gum vigorously. Aman Hakim Khan was lucky first ball, no such luck the 2nd time, comes down the track and tries a highly ambitious slog to leg, this overspinner slides across and he is not to the pitch, sliced off a thick outside-edge and an easy catch for cover. Suddenly DC have lost half their side with Washington Sundar taking three in one over. Aman Hakim Khan c Abhishek Sharma b Washington Sundar 4(2) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Mitchell Marsh, out Lbw!! To the naked eye at first glance, it looked really close and probably even out. A good review and umpire Jayaraman Madanagopal decision has to be overturned. Pitches in line, on a short of length on middle, beats the inside-edge on the defence and thuds into the back leg. Right in front and going on to strike with three reds. Mitchell Marsh is disappointed as he walks back. Mitchell Marsh lbw b T Natarajan 25(15) [4s-5]

Commentary Text: Bhuvneshwar to Philip Salt, out Caught by Klaasen!! Edged and gone. Philip Salt goes for a golden duck. Lovely outswinger outside off, Salt plays a poor shot, pushing away from the body with an open face, regulation outside-edge and Klaasen does the rest. Commentary Text: Ishant to Tripathi, out Caught by Philip Salt!! Was there a nick? Confident appeal and up goes the finger. Tripathi stands and has a look at the umpire before walking off. 139.8kph, on a good length and around the fifth stump zone. Tripathi looks to play a booming drive through the covers sans any feet movement. Gets a faint outside edge and that's been pouched by the keeper. The impact player's streaky knock comes to an end. Tripathi c Philip Salt b Ishant 15(21)

Commentary Text: Axar to Mayank, out Caught by Aman Hakim Khan!! In the air and taken! Smart bowling from Axar Patel. 82.8kph, he saw the batsman step out of his crease and looped it up in the air. Mayank shimmies down the track and is beaten in the flight, he isn't close to the pitch of the ball and goes through with his loft. Miscues it as he's a bit early into the shot. Hardly any power behind it and Aman takes a safe catch after coming forward from long-on. Mayank c Aman Hakim Khan b Axar 49(39) [4s-7]
